Even or Odd
Pseudo code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare X
3)	Input X =   ”enter the number:”
4)	If X < 0 then 
           Print “negative numbers can be even or odd” 
5)	Else If X % 2 == 0 then
         Print   X+” is a Even Number”
6)	Else
         Print   X +” is a Odd Number” 
7)	End

Largest Number in Three numbers
       Pseudo Code :
1)	Start
2)	Declare X , Y , Z
3)	Input X =”enter the first Number:”
4)	Input Y =” enter the second Number:”
5)	Input Z =” enter the Third Number:”
6)	If X==Y AND Y==Z then 
               Print All values are equal 
7)	Else if (X > Y AND X > Z ) then 
                   Print   X + “is largest Number”
8)	else if ( Y > X AND Y > Z ) then 
                  Print   Y + “is largest Number”
9)	else 
                  Print   Z + “ is largest Number”
10)	End

Sum of Numbers from 1 to N
      Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare N, Sum = 0
3)	Input N =”enter the Number”
4)	If N > 0 then
5)	For i = 1 to N increment by 1 
6)	Sum = Sum + i
7)	Print Sum 
8)	Else
           Print “ Invalid Input”
9)	End
                  
Factorial of a Number
Pseudo code :
1)	Start
2)	Declare N, Fact = 1
3)	Input N =”enter the Number”
4)	If N >0 then
5)	For  i =1 to N increment by 1 
6)	Fact = Fact * i
7)	Print Fact 
8)	Else 
          Negative numbers can’t exists
9)	End 
Check Prime Number
    Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num , Count =0
3)	Input Num =”enter the Number”
4)	If Num >1 then 
For  i =2 to Num-1 increment by 1
If Num % i ==0 then 
               Count ++
If Count == 0 then 
           Print   Num +”is a Prime “
Else
          Print   Num +”is not a Prime”
Else
          Print “Number must greater than 1”
5)	End

Print Multiplication Table
     Pseudo code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num 
3)	Input Num = ”enter the Number for multiplication table”
4)	If Num >=1 then
5)	For i =1 to 10 increment by 1
6)	Print Num +”x”+ i +”=” Num*i
7)	Else 
           Print “Invalid Input”
8)	End 

Reverse a Number
 Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num,Rev =0,digit
3)	Input Num =”enter the minimum two digit  number which is going to be reversed”
4)	If Num > 0 then
5)	While Num != 0 
         Digit = Num % 10 
        Rev = Rev * 10 + digit
       Num = Num //10
6)	Print Rev
7)	Else
         Print “Invalid Input”
8)	End

Count Digits in a Number
          Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num, Count =0
3)	Input Num =”enter the Number”
4)	If Num == 0 then 
                 Count = 1
5)	Else
           Num = absolute value of Num
6)	While Num != 0
               Num = Num //10
               Count ++
7)	Print “the no of digits in a number”+ Count
8)	End

Fibonacci Series
        Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare n,Num1 = 0,Num2=1,Num3
3)	Input n =”enter the range of a number”
4)	Print Num1 , Num2 
5)	If n >2 then
6)	For  i =2 to n increment by 1
7)	Num3 = Num1 + Num2
8)	Print Num3
9)	Num1 = Num2
10)	Num2 = Num3
11)	Else
               Exist
12)	End

Check Palindrome Number
         Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num,Rev =0,Digit,OriginalNum.
3)	Input Num =”enter the number which is going to be reversed”
4)	Set OriginalNum = num
5)	While Num != 0
         Digit = Num % 10
        Rev = Rev * 10 + digit
       Num = Num //10
6)	If Rev == OriginalNum then 
                Print “the number is palindrome”+OriginalNum
7)	Else
             Print “the number is not a Palindrome”+ OriginalNum
8)	End

Sum of Even Numbers
              Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare N, Sum =0
3)	Input N = “enter the range “
4)	If N > 0 then 
5)	For i=1 to N increment by 1
6)	If i % 2 == 0 then
          Sum = Sum + i
7)	 Print Sum 
8)	Else 
           Print “Invalid Input”
9)	End

Grade Calculator
Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Marks, Grade =””
3)	Input Marks= ”enter the marks”
4)	If Marks > 0 AND Marks <=100 then
5)	   If Marks >=90 AND Marks <=100  then 
                                  Grade=”A”
  Else if Marks >= 80 AND Marks <=89  then 
                                Grade =”B”
  Else if Marks >= 70 AND Marks <= 79 then 
                                Grade =”C”
  Else if Marks >= 60 AND Marks <= 69 then 
                                 Grade = “D”
  Else if Marks < 60
                                Grade =”F”
                   Else 
          Print “invalid input”

6)	Print Grade.
7)	End

Print Pattern
               Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare Num,
3)	Input Num =”enter the Number”
4)	If Num >0 then 
5)	For i =0 to Num increment by 1
           For j=0  to  i  increment by 1 
                   Print “*”
                  Print  new line
Else 
            Exist
6)	End     
          Simple Calculator 
                 Pseudo Code:
1)	Start
2)	Declare num1 , num2 , op 
3)	Input num1 = “enter the first number:”
4)	Input num2 =”enter the  second number:”
5)	Input op = “enter the operator “
6)	If op =”+” then 
         print  num1 + num2
else if op =”-“
         print num1 – num2 
else if op =”*”
        print num1* num2
else if op =”/”
         if  num2 != 0   then 
                     print num1/ num2 
        Else 
                    Print “Cannot divide by zero” 
7)	Else 
                Print “invalid operator”
8)	End
